HEADWORD: Hydrometeor
<hw>Hy`dro*me"te*or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>meteor</ets>.]</ety> <def>A meteor or
atmospheric phenomenon dependent upon the vapor of water; -- in the
<pluf>pl.</pluf>, a general term for the whole aqueous phenomena of the
atmosphere, as rain, snow, hail, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Nichol.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

